The interceptor now accepts an options object with an optional `headerName` property, defaulting to `'X-Response-Time'`:

```typescript
// Default header name
app.useGlobalInterceptors(new TimingInterceptor());

// Custom header name
app.useGlobalInterceptors(new TimingInterceptor({ headerName: 'X-Request-Duration' }));
```

`threshold` is optional — when omitted the header is always added, matching the previous behavior. When set, the header is only added when the elapsed time exceeds it (in ms):

```typescript
// Always add the header (default)
new TimingInterceptor()

// Only add header when response takes longer than 200ms
new TimingInterceptor({ threshold: 200 })

// Custom header name + threshold
new TimingInterceptor({ headerName: 'X-Request-Duration', threshold: 500 })
```

